-- BBC Middle East Editor Bowen Wounded in Cairo Protests, PA Says
-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 2013-07-06T06:43:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-06/bbc-middle-east-editor-bowen-wounded-in-cairo-protests-pa-says.html
Veteran British reporter Jeremy
Bowen, the  BBC ’s Middle East editor, was shot and wounded while
covering the military coup in Egypt yesterday, the Press
Association said.  Bowen was shown having his head bandaged in a
photograph posted on Twitter, the news agency reported.  “I’ve been hit by a couple of shotgun pellets,” Bowen
said in a message on the site. “Am fine and heading out.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Harrison in London at 
